
Components used in Simulation:
Hardware components:
-	ESP32 – Microcontroller that acts as the brain of the system; processes sensor data, runs control logic and provides Wi-Fi connectivity
-	DS1307 RTC Module – Provides real-time accurate time which is used to time stamp the temperature reading
-	DHT22 Sensor – Measures the ambient temperature and relative humidity; has a wider range of readings and applicable for industrial environments than DHT11 sensor
-	LED – Visual indicator for warning of exceeded temperature
-	Resistor - To protect the LED from burning from excess voltage
Software Components:
-	Wokwi – Online simulation platform used to design the circuit
-	Wokwi Code Editor – Program of the code is written and uploaded to the ESP32
-	ThingSpeak – Online cloud environment used to transmit data from ESP32 
-	GitHub – Documentation of project along with source code
